## 🧠 **简介.**  Rox is a strongly-typed, tree-walk interpreter, implemented in Rust.

Based on the excellent book [Crafting Interpreters](https://craftinginterpreters.com/) by Bob Nystrom, this implementation diverges to Rust patterns, focusing on memory safety, strict type checking, and a robust error-handling architecture.

### 🎯 **地址.** [https://github.com/inblossoms/rox](https://github.com/inblossoms/rox).

### 🪄 **贡献参与.** [https://github.com/inblossoms/rox/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING_zh.md](https://github.com/inblossoms/rox/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING_zh.md).

### 🌟 **Usage.**

**1. REPL Mode (Interactive)**
Run without arguments to start the interactive shell:

```bash
cargo run
```

```javascript
> var a = "Hello";
> print a + " World";
Hello World
```

**2. Script Mode**
Run a `.rox` file:

```bash
cargo run -- scripts/fibonacci.rox
```

#### 📝 Syntax Examples

**Classes and Inheritance:**

```javascript
class Doughnut {
  cook() {
    print "Fry until golden brown.";
  }
}

class BostonCream < Doughnut {
  cook() {
    super.cook();
    print "Pipe full of custard.";
  }
}

BostonCream().cook();
```

**Closures:**

```javascript
fun makeCounter() {
  var i = 0;
  fun count() {
    i = i + 1;
    print i;
  }
  return count;
}

var counter = makeCounter();
counter(); // "1"
counter(); // "2"
```

**Bitwise Operations & Control Flow:**

```javascript
var flags = 5; // 0101
var mask = 1;  // 0001

if ((flags & mask) == 1) {
    print "Bit is set!";
}

for (var i = 0; i < 10; i += 1) {
    if (i % 2 == 0) continue;
    print i;
}
```
